    <h3>Fruiting Body vs. Mycelium: The Quality Difference That Matters</h3>

    <p>The single most important quality indicator in mushroom supplements is whether the product uses fruiting body extracts or mycelium-on-grain. Fruiting body extracts contain the highest concentrations of beta-glucans, hericenones (lion's mane), cordycepin (cordyceps), and triterpenoids (reishi) — the bioactive compounds responsible for clinically demonstrated benefits. Mycelium-on-grain products grow the mycelium on rice or oat grain substrates, and the final product often contains 50-70% grain starch with diluted mushroom compounds. Look for "fruiting body extract" on labels and verify beta-glucan content (ideally 20%+ by dry weight).</p>

