    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Mushroom Coffee Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What are mushroom coffee gummies?</summary><p>Functional mushroom extracts (lion's mane, cordyceps, chaga) combined with 25-50mg caffeine for focus and energy without the coffee crash. The mushrooms provide cognitive and energy benefits through non-stimulant pathways.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How much caffeine do they contain?</summary><p>Most contain 25-50mg — about one-quarter to one-half a cup of coffee. Some are completely caffeine-free.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Which mushrooms are used?</summary><p>Lion's mane (focus/NGF), cordyceps (energy/ATP), chaga (antioxidant), reishi (immune/calm), and turkey tail (immune/gut).</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Do they actually improve focus?</summary><p>Lion's mane improved cognitive scores in a 16-week RCT. Cordyceps improved exercise performance. Effects are both acute and cumulative over 2-8 weeks.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Are they safe?</summary><p>Functional mushrooms have centuries of traditional use and strong modern safety profiles. Avoid if mushroom-allergic. Consult physician if on blood thinners or immunosuppressants.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Fruiting body vs. mycelium — which is better?</summary><p>Fruiting body contains higher concentrations of bioactive compounds. Mycelium-on-grain may contain 50-70% grain filler. Look for "fruiting body extract" and verified beta-glucan content.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I replace morning coffee with these?</summary><p>Yes, with a transition period. Reduce coffee gradually over 1-2 weeks while adding mushroom gummies. Most users report equivalent or better sustained focus after 2-4 weeks.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How long do they take to work?</summary><p>Caffeine: 15-30 minutes. Cordyceps energy: 1-2 weeks. Lion's mane cognition: 2-4 weeks, with peak benefits at 8-16 weeks of consistent use.</p></details>

    <div class="warn-box"><span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span><p><strong>Important:</strong> Individuals with mushroom allergies should avoid these products. If you take blood thinners, consult your physician before taking reishi-containing products. Those with autoimmune conditions should discuss immune-modulating mushrooms with their physician. Pregnant and nursing women should consult their healthcare provider.</p></div>

